{"id": "duc04-testb-40:0#2", "contents": "North Korean officials, including Vice Defense Minister Jong Chang Ryol, have issued strong statements threatening war against the United States. Ryol was quoted as saying that the North Korean military would \"blow up the U.S. territory as a whole\" if the US starts a war on the Korean Peninsula. Other officials, including party members and plant managers, have also pledged to take drastic action, including \"thousandfold revenge\" and arming themselves with the \"spirit of human bombs and of suicidal attack.\" The North Korean military, with 1.1 million troops, forms the backbone of the government, with leader Kim Jong Il ruling the country as the head of the military."}
